HEADWORD: Cataphracted
<hw>Cat"a*phract`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Covered with a cataphract, or armor of plates, scales, etc.; or
with that which corresponds to this, as horny or bony plates, hard,
callous skin, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cataphractic</ent>⟦br⟧
